Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_metric_config(25.10)                              get_metric_config(25.10)

Name
       get_metric_config - Gets the current metric configuration setting

Syntax
       get_metric_config

       -help

       -format {html excel text}

       Gets the current metric configuration setting.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each get_metric_config parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_metric_config

       -format {html excel text}
              Specifies configuration for the specified report_metric format.

              Data_type: enum, optional

Example
       The following prints the current defined pages, heading and tables:

       foreach page_name [dict keys [get_metric_config ]] {

         puts "\nPage : $page_name"

         puts "--------------------------------------------"

         foreach page [dict get [get_metric_config] $page_name] {

           foreach key [dict keys $page] {

             if {($key == "id")} {

               set id [dict get $page $key]

             }

             if {($key == "component")} {

                puts "$key : $id ([dict get $page $key])"

             }

           }

         }

       }

